article.description: Brynton Lemar scored 19 points, 12 from 3-point range, and Lawrence White and Chima Moneke each scored 14 and UC Davis upended Hawaii 68-59 on Thursday.
article.headline: Lemar's 3's propel UC Davis past Hawaii 68-59
article.linkText: Lemar's 3's propel UC Davis past Hawaii 68-59
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. -- Brynton Lemar scored 19 points, 12 from 3-point range, and Lawrence White and Chima Moneke each scored 14 and UC Davis upended Hawaii 68-59 on Thursday. Hawaii shot just one free throw in the game; a miss by Gibson Johnson. Lemar's 3-pointer with 7:30 left gave UC Davis (19-11, 11-4 Big West) the lead for good at 49-47. On Hawaii's next possession, Lemar came up with a steal and promptly buried another 3 and the Aggies took control. UC Davis shot 26 for 57 (45.6 percent) from the floor, including 8 for 23 from 3-point range. Darius Graham added 10 points in the win, which set up its first-place showdown with UC Irvine (18-13, 11-4) on Saturday. Jack Purchase led Hawaii with 15 points shooting 5 for 11 exclusively behind the 3-point arc. Noah Allen scored 13 points and Johnson added 12.
